html:
THIS IS A HOMEPAGE.

Frame is the notebook that talks back! üòÉüç∫

FRAME WILL ALLOW YOU TO DO GREAT THINGS.
  1. Like, getting informed answers within the context of your notes, from questions you ask in natural language.
  2. And, automatically generating summaries of your data as you save, allowing you to easily navigate your entries to find and study the most important parts.
  3. Also, extracting key items of information like names, dates, phone numbers, and other entities, and outputting visualizations in a seamless dashboard!

Just click the Ask / Analyze tab to immediately see what Frame has to offer!

Download the app at http://github.com/jddunn/frame now while it's fresh and buggy still! (So don't be clicking through your entries too fast or it'll stress out). Or, you can use Frame right now, on this site, to store and export your entries. Warning: This is a temporary site host for Frame, so you must export your data and save it to your computer, or it will be eventually removed.
